<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>Sponsorship - FTC Starter Hub</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/main.css?v=13">
</head>
<body>
  <header></header>
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Sponsorship Templates</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Ready-to-use email and letter templates for approaching sponsors and donors.
      </p>
      <a href="/resources" class="btn btn-secondary back-button">← Back to Resources</a>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Sponsorship Inquiry Email</h2>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p><strong>Subject:</strong> Partnership Opportunity - FTC Team [Team Number]</p>
          <p>Dear [Business Name],</p>
          <p>We are Team [Number] – [Team Name], a robotics team competing in the FIRST Tech Challenge. We're reaching out because your company's values align with our mission to inspire students in STEM.</p>
          <p>Our team needs support for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Competition registration and travel</li>
            <li>Robot parts and tools</li>
            <li>Team development and training</li>
          </ul>
          <p>In return, we offer:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Logo placement on robot and team materials</li>
            <li>Social media recognition</li>
            <li>Company mention in outreach events</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Would you be interested in supporting our team? We'd love to discuss partnership opportunities.</p>
          <p>Sincerely,<br>[Your Name]<br>[Your Position]<br>[Contact Information]</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Corporate Sponsorship Letter</h2>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>[Your School Letterhead]</p>
          <p>[Date]</p>
          <p>[Business Address]</p>
          <p>Dear [Decision Maker Name],</p>
          <p>We are writing to request your company's sponsorship of Team [Number], an FTC robotics team from [School/Organization].</p>
          <p><strong>About Our Team:</strong><br>
          Founded in [Year], our team has [achievements/competition record]. We compete in regional and state competitions, bringing home awards and recognition.</p>
          <p><strong>Why Support STEM Education:</strong><br>
          Robotics teaches problem-solving, teamwork, and innovation. By sponsoring us, your company invests in future engineers and leaders.</p>
          <p><strong>Sponsorship Investment:</strong><br>
          We're seeking $[Amount] to cover robot parts ($1,200), competition fees ($400), and travel ($600).</p>
          <p><strong>Recognition:</strong><br>
          Your company will receive logo placement on our robot, website, and team shirts.</p>
          <p>We'd appreciate the opportunity to discuss how your company can support STEM education. Feel free to contact us at [phone/email].</p>
          <p>Sincerely,<br>[Team Coach Name]<br>FTC Team [Number]</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Donation Request (Parents/Community)</h2>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>Dear Family &amp; Friends,</p>
          <p>Our FTC team is preparing for an exciting season of robotics competition! To make this possible, we need your support.</p>
          <p><strong>What We're Raising For:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Robot parts and electronics - $1,200</li>
            <li>Competition registration - $400</li>
            <li>Travel to tournaments - $600</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Every donation, no matter the size, helps us build a better robot and provide incredible learning opportunities for our team members.</p>
          <p><strong>How to Donate:</strong><br>
          • Online: [Link]<br>
          • Check: Made out to [Organization], memo "Team [Number]"<br>
          • Contact: [Email]</p>
          <p>Thank you for believing in our team!</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Grant Application Template Sections</h2>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Project Summary (200 words)</h3>
          <p>Describe your team, mission, and what you're building this season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Problem Statement (200 words)</h3>
          <p>Explain the financial challenges and why funding is critical.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Goals &amp; Objectives (300 words)</h3>
          <p>Outline specific, measurable goals for the season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Budget Justification (200 words)</h3>
          <p>Break down exactly how funds will be used with specific quotes/estimates.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Impact &amp; Outcomes (300 words)</h3>
          <p>Describe how this funding will help students and your community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Sustainability (100 words)</h3>
          <p>Explain your long-term funding strategy beyond this grant.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Thank You Letter Template</h2>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>Dear [Sponsor/Donor Name],</p>
          <p>Thank you so much for your generous donation of $[Amount] to Team [Number]!</p>
          <p>Your support directly enabled us to [specific impact - build new mechanism, compete in state competition, etc.]. This means the world to our team members.</p>
          <p>We're excited to share our progress with you. Please follow us on social media (@Team[Number]) to see updates and meet our team members.</p>
          <p>We hope to continue our partnership in the future. If you have any questions about our team or season, please don't hesitate to reach out.</p>
          <p>With gratitude,<br>[Team Coach Name]<br>Team [Number]</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Pro Tips</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Personalize each message - avoid mass-sent templates</li>
          <li>Be specific about needs and dollar amounts</li>
          <li>Highlight impact and student benefits, not just robot parts</li>
          <li>Always follow up with gratitude</li>
          <li>Keep sponsors updated throughout the season</li>
          <li>Provide ROI - show them how their money helps</li>
          <li>Build long-term relationships, not one-time asks</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script src="/assets/js/main.js?v=37"></script>
</body>
</html>
